rComments: If you care about your GPA, RUN! She makes her exams unnecessarily hard. I'm not sure why she makes a first-year course harder than it's supposed to be. Before taking the class, I read her reviews and all of them are true. I was varying of her exams but even if you prepare, chances are that you will still not be able to do the long answers.

I personally would not take this class. Lectures were long and boring, some of the later questions on exams were hard just for the sake of being hard, & not relevant to what we learned in class. All tests were at 8:30 on Saturday instead of later in the day. Makes you buy a $100 assignment service instead of posting the assignments on Brightspace.
she explains the course very clearly but when it comes to her tests, she asks too many questions, and her questions are tricky so the best advice is to study harder for your exams.

Awful prof. Her midterms are nothing like what she teaches, and her teaching style is average at best. I scored a good grade no thanks to her. Extremely rude and doesn't like to answer questions. The course is easy, but she makes it unnecessarily hard for students. If u can, take this with Elise Critoph instead and thank me later.

my least favourite class, because even when I read the textbook, watched the lectures and attend the tutorials, her tests were so hard that I only could get a 60-70 mark. the practice past midterms she gives is 1000x easier than the ones she gives for the actual midterm. AVOID AT ALL COSTS
as a prof shes not that bad, but her tests are the absolute worst which makes you not like her all that much. avoid at all costs, her exams are deathly.
Very hard class. Tutorials are not helpful, and exam time is very short. Avoid her classes!!!

Her tutorials she provides in this class were absolute trash and not helpful in helping students succeed in this class. Professor Morin whom taught alongside with her was poor too. Avoid both of these professors if you care about your grades in this class.

Professor Blanco-Perez has no path when it came to teaching the course, it was often all over the place. Her lectures has limited relation to the weekly quizzes and assignments she provides, they are all based off the weekly tutorials that are different than the course material of the week. Her final exam was just confusing and difficult.

I wanna give you a zero, but that's not possible so I give you a one. DO NOT TAKE HER. Trust (if you care about your grades and your mental health). She is mean when responding to emails and sometimes just not answer you.
Just avoid her. I cried after every lecture and quiz. The assignments were hard for no reason as well. The final seemed easier but trust her to grade terribly.

I absolutely loved this teacher! So nice! You can tell she loves what she's teaching. Her teaching was pre-recorded lectures but they were seriously so good. She explains the material SO well. I absolutely love her! The best prof I ever had in regards to teaching. The tests are hard, you do need to study! she was also always available for help.
Differ your class if its with her shes not worth your time

Her lectures are amazing, she explains things so well without dragging it on or boring us. Microeconomics is a very difficult course and she made the content much easier to learn. Would take again in a heartbeat.
Her teaching is normal but mid-term and the exam was so hard. I took ECO 1102 with a different professor and her teaching was superb. Plus mid-term and final were fair.
Teaches the material well. Exam and midterm kinda hard.

She's a nice professor, I do enjoy her class, but I don't like her quizzes and exams. She doe have office hours, but questions asked through email will not be answered. The way how quizzes are being calculated is not a good way at all. Exams are a bit tough and very tricky. Also, the second assignment is extremely hard compared to the first one.
Horrendous professor, and an absolute disgrace to uottawas reputation. Never in my 21 years of academic discourse have I had a professor as horrible as her.
Very average professor. Makes the lectures uninteresting.
Go for another prof if you can! she's too difficult and very hard to reach! She sets her students up to not pass

First, you have to buy a 80-100$ platform for the class. I had her + Gordon Lenjosek and she was better. Her lectures are a reasonable length and not painful to watch. However, she's hard to reach through office hours + didn't really answer emails. You'd only get help from TAs. The midterms/finals are hard and loaded yet practice tests were useless

Her lectures were easy to follow, and helped clarify content in the textbook. The class was asynchronous so I did not have a lot of personal interaction with her. From what I can see she is an average professor
Horrible teacher, her tests are really weird and she tries to keep as much information from you as possible. its like she wants her students to fail....
Her lectures are BASICALLY (she overuses this word) the textbook. Assigments everyweek. Heavy course. Hard to understand the material of the class. very hard exam
Horrible professor, tries to gate keep her test questions, assignments, and quizzes. I have never had a professor who looks to trick students rather then test knowledge

Nice lady, okay as a prof. Has an accent but it wasn't too hard to understand. She explained the material but you're probably better off just reading the textbook (which is mandatory, there's weekly assignments based off of it on connect). Exams were hard.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Test heavy', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: just not a fan - she co-taught with LP Morin and the class was completely asynchronus with lectures posted at the very beginning of the semester (slides had summer 2020 written on them) so the effort just seemed minimal; definitely had to do a lot of practice bc minimal support from prof, not a very accessible class (basically a self-taught class)

she made the class very boring and heavy and I do not like her because it was very unnecessary and she sets students up to fail. Tutorial quizzes are terribly framed and you cannot go back to check your answers on a times quiz and homeworks are hard
Probably the worst prof I've had in the department so far. She does not think about the students and tries to make an easy class harder for no reason at all. Try your luck with another prof

rComments: Same energy with Gordon which means take other professors.
not a very fair professor, makes you learn on her terms and her assignments and tests are very confusing
She is ridiculous! Stuff is easy but her midterms and assignments are extremely confusing. The grading criteria is unclear
Her midterm averages are well below the norm but she refuses to bell curve any assignment or mid term.. good luck
Absolute joke of a professor, the class is easy but she tries to complicate everything. I genuinely can't believe she was hired by the school. Do yourself a favour and switch
Very hard!

Decent prof. She was a good teacher and knew her material but was stuck teaching a very dry class. Microeconomics is a breeze if you plan on taking it as an elective, and I would surely recommend taking it with Cristina if possible.

Don't be afraid of eco with her, she explains the concepts clearly and she spends plenty of time on the important topics that can be on the exam. Exams are based on basic concepts, just participate in lectures.

She may not be the most perfect prof you'll ever get, but do not worry if you have her. She explains things very well one-on-one and as long as you study for a decent amount of time, you'll get a good grade.
The material covered in class was not the same material tested on the midterms and exam. Also, she explained course material by using specific examples rather than discussing the overall concept.

Two midterms are all short answers, non-multiple choice. The second midterm is harder than what I thought. An explanation for what you wrote done not always simple and explanation count for a part of the mark in each question.

Terrible prof, she either said she was not getting the concepts through to the students or that we were not working hard enough. Nothing she taught or focused on was on the written midterm, and she doesn't explain herself and calls people out for having a blank face since she makes no sense.

Basically, and mathematically does not know what she is talking about. Midterms are nothing like the practice. Concepts seem simple in class and during assignments but during testing are given in a way that was never seen before.

If you need to take this course take it with Cristina. she is super sweet, goes slow in class and welcomes questions. she will explain concepts until everyone understands it. she is more concerned with her students understanding than getting through tons of material. 2 midterms are super easy, and the connect assignments are a grade booster!

Do the connect assignments AND the practice assignments!! You paid for connect... might as well use it well. Her midterms are all short answers. Really not that tough, but read properly. Her final is all multiple choice. I would suggest doing other prof's practice exams and midterms because they are usually all MC and it's good practice.
Cristina is an very nice lady with an great marking scheme, do not listen to all the bad reviews. However, her lectures are boring and final is not impossible if you study very hard.

The midterms were short answer and they were nothing like the examples she would provide or the online quizzes we had to do every week. The final was all multiple choice and the questions were out of nowhere. This class ruined my GPA.

Real tough grader, both 2 mid-terms are short answers and the final is multiple choice Qs. You should be comfortable enough with Math to understand and do well in the course. The prof is always available during office hours. She has the tendency to speed up very quickly at the end of the semester to catch up with the material.

Literally tanked my GPA, assessments are unnecessarily hard and don't follow the examples of what you learn in class; so much of what you need to know is implied and not directly taught. Calc was not a prerec for this class and yet the midterm was 75% calculus. Learned more for this class in ECO 2117 and DVM than in her lectures. AVOID AT ALL COSTS
good prof not necessary to attend

If you're not at good at math, then you're definitely going to struggle in her class. She never revealed the average for the midterm, that's how bad it was. Her midterms aren't multiple choice, which is what makes it even worse. In my opinion, her midterms are hard for no reason. You would think it would be similar to the Connect assignments but no
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Good prof and available during office hours

Her lecture isn't clear and there's no textbook you can study. She gives no feedback on assignments and there aren't any materials to study for the exams. Her exams are also hard and doesn't reflect the assignments. And she takes attendance so you have to go to her boring lectures.

Christina is definitely the best professor in my first semester of school. She was kind, and at the same time made it clear that the purpose of her class is not to give everyone A+, which seems only fair. The line to her office hours was always long as she took time to answer all the questions students had, and she's also always available by email.
Beware

She is an amazing professor. She explains everything very well and she is wiling to reexplain if someone did not understand. Her midterm was mostly easy. She really cares about the students and she want to make sure that they are understanding what she is trying to explain. Do not hesitate to take her class.

She's nice and looks like she cares about her students but I found her exams did NOT reflect what she emphasizes in class. For ex, in stats our second midterm was 2 chapters and he said "Focus on chapter 4."  There was literally one from ch. 4 on the midterm. She bell curved the grades and still wouldn't tell us the average because it was so low.

Mostly she just read the ppt at the lecture and gave nothing useful in the exam. She usually gave high grade for your assignments and pretty low grade for your exams, and the final was tough and obvious not fair. I know she tried to be a good teacher, but I think she should care more about her students.

I really liked her! You can tell she enjoys teaching! Unfortunately, she does rant a bit too much at times. Many times when we were taking up an assignment she would spend half an hour just taking up the multiple choice and we wouldn't have time to look over the harder questions. Overall, she is a great prof, a fair marker, and a wonderful person!

I absolutely LOVE Christina! She's one of those profs who have a real impact on the way you view life. On the first day she showed us a job description for UN which was inspiring  to see. She really cares about her students and takes the time to learn their names and also has a kickass motivational pep talk just when you need it!
Excellent professor. Knows her stuff and will help you during her office hours. You get a great mark if you attend!
She was a ok prof. Nice person, but i  don't  think she is good at teaching.
